  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6595.95 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-7.4B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+12.6B), dealers are in a critical inflection zone where they'll aggressively buy any dip toward 6590 but immediately start selling pressure above 6605. The massive 117% GEX surge and recent regime flip into PIN mode indicates dealers have rebuilt their long gamma positions and will now provide stabilizing flows, capping upside momentum while supporting downside moves. Key battleground is this tight 6590-6605 range with the 6598 flip level acting as the fulcrum—expect violent whipsaw action until price breaks definitively above 6610 or below 6580.\n\n**Bottom line:** Price should ping-pong aggressively between 6590-6610 with limited breakout potential.",
